New Records: Immanuel Quickley made 15 assists and scored 21 points in his first game back after missing 22 games with an injury.
Key Match Events: The Raptors had a 25-6 run in the fourth quarter, capped by a 29-foot three-pointer by Quickley.
Scottie Barnes led all scorers with 33 points and 13 rebounds.
Pre-Game Insights: The Raptors were without swingman RJ Barrett due to illness, but his imminent return was expected to help turn around the team's season.
Coach Darko Rajakovic mentioned that Barrett's return could make the team more dangerous.
Post-Match Reflections: Immanuel Quickley expressed gratitude for being back on the court after missing 22 games with an injury.
Quickley said that being back on the court with his teammates and coaches is a different feeling than being on the sidelines.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Raptors beat the Brooklyn Nets 130-113, snapping an 11-game losing skid.
Immanuel Quickley re-signed with the Raptors on a five-year, $175-million contract last July.
Others: The Raptors' starting lineup has not been complete all season, and they are awaiting the return of several key players, including RJ Barrett and Gradey Dick.
